## 7. Learning Flow (Pedagogical Structure)

```
[Story Intro] → [Concept 1: Addition] → [Simulation 1] → [Concept 2: Subtraction]
→ [Simulation 2] → [Combined Concept] → [Simulation 3] → [Practice Quiz] → [Badge & Celebration]
```

### Phase 1: Learning (≈ 10 minutes)
Story scenes, narrated explanations, and interactive simulations. No pressure, no scoring.

### Phase 2: Guided Practice (≈ 5 minutes)
3 scaffolded questions with hints enabled, step-by-step visual feedback.

### Phase 3: Independent Practice (≈ 5–8 minutes)
10 fully randomised questions, timed per question (optional), scored, with immediate visual feedback.

### Phase 4: Celebration
Badge award, XP total, stars earned, option to replay.

