## 11. Visual & UX Design Principles

The design **strictly follows** the visual language established in `equal-tau.vercel.app` and the `dsamyak/equal` GitHub repository:

- **Colour palette:** Warm, saturated primaries on a soft cream/white background; consistent with Intellia SG brand
- **Typography:** Rounded, friendly sans-serif (matching existing Intellia lessons)
- **Illustrations:** Flat cartoon style, culturally neutral characters (John, Sarah, Mike, Priya represented with abstract avatars/colours, not ethnicity-specific features)
- **Animations:** Smooth CSS transitions, spring physics for drag interactions, no jarring cuts
- **Layout:** Card-based scene containers; full-width simulation panels; bottom-fixed progress bar
- **Buttons:** Large, colourful CTA buttons with hover/press states (touch-friendly ≥ 44px targets)
- **Feedback:** Immediate inline; no modal popups interrupting flow

